'''Å½iÄe''' is a [[village]] in the [[Slovenske Konjice]] [[municipality]] in eastern [[Slovenia]]. It lies on the right bank of the river [[Dravinja]] near its conflunece with the ''Å½iÄnica'' stream, a minor right tributary that flows just south of the village. It is best known for the [[Å½iÄe Charterhouse]], a 12th century monastery that is not actually in the settlement, but 6 kilometres further up the valley Å½iÄnica stream. The area is part of the traditional region of [[Lower Styria]]. The municipality is now included in the [[Savinjska statistical region|Savinja statistical region]].<ref>[http://www.slovenskekonjice.si Slovenske Konjice Municipality site]</ref>
The [[parish church]] in the settlement is dedicated to [[Saint Peter]] and belongs to the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Maribor]]. It is a 14th century church that was rebuilt in 1660.<ref>[http://rkd.situla.org/ Slovenian Ministry of Culture register of national heritage] reference number eÅ¡d 3543</ref>
== Tourism ==
* '''1998''' The village won the prestigious European [[Entente Florale]] Bronze Medal Award.[http://www.entente-florale.eu/efe]
